feat: configurable alert rules engine replacing hardcoded thresholds (fl-v2h)

Replace compile-time alert constants with per-project configurable rules:

DB layer:
- alert_rules table: condition types (threshold, new_issue, regression,
  slow_burn), action types (bead, slack, webhook, email), per-rule
  thresholds and time windows
- alert_history table: records every rule firing with timestamp
- EnsureDefaultAlertRules auto-creates defaults matching current behavior
  (3-in-5min burst, 1 fatal immediate, 1h slow-burn, regression)

Rule engine (gastown/rules.go):
- Per-rule sliding windows for threshold conditions
- Level filtering (error, fatal, any)
- Separate evaluation paths for threshold, regression, and slow-burn

Bridge changes:
- OnEvent now loads per-project rules and evaluates via RuleEngine
- sweepSlowBurn evaluates slow_burn rules per project instead of
  using global SlowBurnAge constant
- Alert history recorded on every rule firing

API endpoints:
- GET/POST /api/{project_id}/alert-rules/ — list and create rules
- GET/PUT/DELETE /api/{project_id}/alert-rules/{rule_id}/ — CRUD
- GET /api/{project_id}/alert-history/ — fired alert log

Dashboard:
- Settings page shows alert rules table and recent alert history
- Rules display condition, level filter, action type, enabled status

